oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: First Mule Day in Columbia
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Black and white photograph of First Mule Day in Columbia, Tennessee. The view is from South Main Street.

Mule Day originated as an annual mule market, in Columbia, TN, which occurred on the first weekend of April. Livestock breeders from the South East of the United States would come to sell, buy, and trade their mules. Over the years, the celebration has evolved into a large community festival spanning several days which includes: mule and livestock events, parades, as well as local food, music, and crafts.
